text.tspan: The fighting ability of Quasars is not enough to
stand against the empire because they lack
asymmetric power like the Titan. However, there
is a good chance of defeating other battles if the
empire does not have the Titan on the
battlefield.
Since the empire has many soldiers, Quasars
fighting ability is excellent, has outstanding
officers, and they have Turner Cobain
leading them. Their combat performance is
outstanding. The knowledge they possess is
from the Imperial days when they could
exert their power with sufficient support.
They are in a position where they must adapt
to command a small elite force and achieve
results.
Quasars have about 5,000
professional soldiers, but because non-
professional soldiers can fight, the
entire group of 20,000 can be
considered a resistance group.
Turner led his army, newly joined
empire soldiers, and even civilians to
the west. They were out of reach from
the empire, to establish a base for the
resistance. They established a group of
rebels that fights against the empire.
Since then, those who were wary of the
empire’s expansion or had already been
harmed by the Empire’s sword have
joined the Quasars.
Turner Cobain, an old Fidelian Empire general,
became the leader of the resistance called
Quasars. The Quasars is an independent
organization that rebels against the Fidelian
Empire.
Gary uses connections inside and outside the
Empire to team up with other assassin groups
for joint operations when a large-scale force is
unavoidably required.
All lounge staff members are professional
killers with sufficient combat expertise of an
entire army platoon. However, because they
lack superhuman abilities and their armed
forces are trained specifically for surprise,
disturbance, and assassination that emphasize
confidentiality, they are unsuited for large-
scale conflicts.
Many people fear her because her family
has been honing and passing down their
unique killing techniques since ancient
times, and her killing skills are at a level
that does not tarnish the family’s name.
During his time in the military,
Gary was a highly skilled
assassin and mercenary, but
now that he’s retired, he lacks
the strength to fight. Instead,
Misa, a half-Japanese-
Caucasian bartender always
supports Gary and defends him
at all costs. She is his most
trusted employee.
Although Gary Haddenberg is the captain, there is a culture
in the lounge where employees have the freedom of speech to
voice their opinions without fear of repercussions when they
advance to a more critical position within the company.
Each member of
Gary’s Lounge is
in charge of a
specific position
because it is a
minority, and the
distribution of
each role is done
so.
Due to his frequent interactions with empire-
wide traders, Gary has easy access to
information. These traders provide access to
general information, and “advanced”
information is frequently obtained from
special people like imperial officials, corporate
representatives, and military officials.
Usually, this information is sold for a very high
price, therefore running the pub is financially
easy. The ten or so clerks are all professional
hitmen that Gary knows personally and
because he wants to maintain it in that way,
he doesn’t hire or increase staff.
In the unlikely event that the company needs
to hire new employees due to death or for
another reason, Gary is strict with the
interview process for new recruits because he
needs to understand their capabilities of
taking on dangerous responsibilities and roles
under any conditions. Additionally, once a
member joins, the member cannot leave at
any time, and withdrawal is only permitted in
a small number of unique circumstances.
Even when someone has knowledge of Gary’s
Lounge, they frequently only have a limited
understanding of it, and very few of them are
aware of the assassination plot.
Gary’s Lounge was
established by a former
assassin named Gary
Haddenberg. Although
it’s in a shape of a pub
and is currently open,
sales of intelligence and
information generate
most of it’s income.
They carry out
assassination missions
for a few clients and sell
information obtained by
mediating between
various organizations to
receive funds or fulfill
requests.
New beginnings
Their military might is enough to make even
veterans with moderate fighting skills
tremble, and some estimate that only a few
thousand will be able to deal with half of
Fidelia’s entire army. Kin manages sufficient
operating funds to secure adequate weapons
and distributes standard weapons so that
there is no significant difference in combat
power between new and veteran
mercenaries.
Obtaining weapons for mercenaries to use
individually was a kind of an iron rule in
the post-war era. Still, since the current
Kossacks are actively receiving Fidelia’s
support, a certain amount of ‘welfare’s
guaranteed in that area. As the most
outstanding primary combat power, this
generous procurement of military support
made them the strongest army of all
current factions.
Whether you are Kin or an
officer, you cannot issue an
order that directly contradicts
the will of the employer who
commissioned you in each
battle. Trust is directly related
to life as a mercenary.
Kin is the commander, and he
commands all three battalions. All
three battalions consist of about 50
soldiers and 1 leader; each called a
battalion officer. During the battle, the
battalion officers determine the
situation of each battle in an extremely
detailed manner. When Kin receives a
commission from the empire, his only
role is to distribute tasks to his
battalions accordingly.
This overwhelming fighting power,
however, is sometimes accepted as an
arrogant image by others. They show a
significantly condescending attitude
toward those with less fighting power
than themselves. This attitude is
repulsive not only to Fidelia’s citizens but
also to the Imperial Army of Fidelia.
However, because their armed forces are
so outstanding, they do not engage in
socially controversial acts. It’s not easy to
show hostility towards Kossacks, even
within Fidelia.
Kin Verlice gathered the
scattered mercenaries and
united them, establishing their
identity as Kossacks. Each
mercenary unit in the
organization has a different
story and direction. Despite
their various features, they
have one trait: their combat
power is truly ‘overwhelmingly’
powerful.
The Kossacks, known as the
faction with the most
dominant fighting skills, such
as melee combat and
marksmanship, tend to
maintain the image of a unit
worthy of this reputation.
From the outside, they appear
cold and frightening, the
mercenary team devoid of
emotion due to their
systematic, thoroughly
educated manner. They don’t
usually show much emotion,
and they are infinitely
mechanical, relentless, and
ruthless regarding their goals.
Temporarily, the Kossacks are
solely working for the empire.
